#MEM id=maslow-copy source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/custom/maslow-copy/SKILL.md
M|maslow-copy|name: maslow-copy
M|maslow-copy|description: Maps Maslow's 5 need levels to specific copy angles for Novizio and Hourbour. Use to select the psychological register before writing any cg copy.
M|maslow-copy|version: 1.0.0
M|maslow-copy|Every piece of copy speaks to a need level — consciously or not. Choosing the wrong level wastes the message on an audience that's operating at a different register. This skill makes the selection exp
M|maslow-copy|| Level | Need | Novizio Angle | Hourbour Angle |
M|maslow-copy||-------|------|---------------|----------------|
M|maslow-copy|| **1 — Physiological** | Basic survival | Out of scope | Out of scope |
M|maslow-copy|| **2 — Safety** | sec, stability, certainty | Quality guarantee, lasting construction | Certainty over hours and money. "Always know." |
M|maslow-copy|| **3 — Belonging** | Community, identity, affiliation | The editorial set. Worn by people who know. | Join the professionals who track their time. |
M|maslow-copy|| **4 — Esteem** | Status, recognition, self-respect | Primary level. Quiet luxury as identity signal. | Professional credibility. The sharp operator. |
M|maslow-copy|| **5 — Self-actualisation** | Growth, expression, becoming | Upper tier. Style as self-expression. Wear what you've become. | Premium tier. Financial clarity as a state of mind. |
M|maslow-copy|**Novizio → Esteem (primary), Self-actualisation (secondary)**
M|maslow-copy|- The Novizio buyer is not buying clothes. They're signalling who they are.
M|maslow-copy|- Copy addresses identity and aspiration, never anxiety or price.
M|maslow-copy|- Do NOT use Safety-level framing (scarcity, FOMO, urgency) — it conflicts with the self-assured tone.
M|maslow-copy|**Hourbour → Safety (primary), Esteem (secondary)**
M|maslow-copy|- The Hourbour user is a professional who wants certainty and control.
M|maslow-copy|- Copy addresses peace of mind, clarity, and professional credibility.
M|maslow-copy|- Safety framing is strongest: "Every hour tracked. Every client paid."
M|maslow-copy|- Esteem framing works in brand copy: "The tool sharp operators use."
M|maslow-copy|- "Always know where your hours went."
M|maslow-copy|- "Every trade, tracked."
M|maslow-copy|- "Built to last. Not built to be replaced."
M|maslow-copy|- "Join 10,000 freelancers who stopped guessing."
M|maslow-copy|- "The pieces worn by the people who know."
M|maslow-copy|- "Dress like you mean it."
M|maslow-copy|- "The professional who tracks everything gains everything."
M|maslow-copy|- "Not for everyone. That's the point."
M|maslow-copy|- "Wear what you've become."
M|maslow-copy|- "Financial clarity isn't a feature. It's a state of mind."
M|maslow-copy|- "This isn't who you want to be. It's who you already are."
M|maslow-copy|1. Before writing any cg copy, identify the target need level.
M|maslow-copy|2. Confirm the level is appropriate for the vtr (see Primary Levels above).
M|maslow-copy|3. Select copy angles from that level's register.
M|maslow-copy|4. If mixing levels (e.g., Safety headline + Esteem body), ensure they don't conflict — Safety + Esteem can coexist; Safety + Self-actualisation creates register confusion.
M|maslow-copy|5. Log the chosen level in the copy delivery brief echo (Communication DNA step 1).